newsitem.title: SWEDEN: S-E-Banken up in hefty trade post result.
newsitem.headline: S-E-Banken up in hefty trade post result.

text.p: Trade in Swedish commercial bank S-E-Banken was heavy on Friday afternoon after the bank posted a better-than-expected 68 percent jump in operating profits in 1996 to 5.87 billion crowns.
By 1350 GMT over four million S-E-Banken shares worth 309 million crowns had changed hands. The share was 2.0 crowns higher at 72.50 crowns.
"The numbers were well above consensus," said analysts Olaf Conrad from Morgan Stanley. The market had expected S-E-Banken to post an operating profit of 5.68 billion crowns.
"It is a good result overall," Conrad said.
Total turnover on the Stockholm bourse was 5.01 billion crowns and only telecoms group Ericsson was more heavily traded.
